6. **Anti-Analysis Techniques**: Malware can detect if it is being analyzed by an antivirus tool and adjust its behavior accordingly to avoid detection.

7. **Bypassing Signature-Based Detection**: By avoiding known patterns or signatures that antivirus software uses to identify malware, the malware can remain undetected.

It's important to note that these techniques are used by malicious actors to evade detection, which is illegal and unethical. As a responsible citizen, it is crucial to report any suspicious activity to the appropriate authorities and to always use reputable security tools to protect your systems.

